WEBVTT

00:07.758 --> 00:09.714
[ Groans ]

00:29.864 --> 00:31.479
[Sighs]

01:09.737 --> 01:11.853
[ Door opens ]

02:10.256 --> 02:12.542
Then call your damn boss!
I need to see her right now!

02:12.550 --> 02:15.212
I told you, you can come back
during visiting hours.

02:15.219 --> 02:16.925
I'm a cop, make the call.

02:16.929 --> 02:19.090
I'm sorry, sir,
but there are no exceptions.

02:19.098 --> 02:20.429
[ Scoffs ]

02:20.433 --> 02:22.264
Your friend is being
taken care of.

02:22.268 --> 02:23.678
She's a danger to herself
right now.

02:23.686 --> 02:25.426
What the hell are you
talking about? Screw this.

02:25.438 --> 02:26.848
- Sir, you need to leave... Now!
- Get out of my...

02:26.856 --> 02:29.097
Hey. Do you want me to make
a call to my friends, huh?

02:29.108 --> 02:30.473
We'll have
a little rumble, huh?

02:30.484 --> 02:31.815
Carlson: - Holder, what the hell are
you doing?! - You want to go?

02:31.819 --> 02:34.060
Sir! Sir,
they're trying to frame her.

02:34.071 --> 02:35.481
We need to get her out of here
right now.

02:35.489 --> 02:37.400
Sarah entered sovereign Indian
land without a warrant...

02:37.408 --> 02:38.648
For that matter, a badge.

02:38.659 --> 02:39.694
I told her
numerous times...

02:39.702 --> 02:41.112
I told both of you
to stay out of there.

02:41.120 --> 02:42.326
I should have taken your badge!

02:42.330 --> 02:44.036
She found evidence
inside the casino

02:44.040 --> 02:46.201
that proves the tribe
is covering up a murder.

02:46.208 --> 02:47.243
Well, let's hope not

02:47.251 --> 02:49.162
because it will be
completely inadmissible.

02:49.170 --> 02:51.206
Look, Chief Jackson said
she attacked a casino worker

02:51.213 --> 02:52.794
because she was
trying to kill herself.

02:52.798 --> 02:56.290
She's not suicidal, sir.
And you know it.

02:56.302 --> 02:58.293
You've seen what
they're capable of!

02:58.304 --> 03:00.636
Only a psychiatrist
can get her out, Holder.

03:00.640 --> 03:02.255
My hands are tied.

03:04.852 --> 03:07.309
All right.

03:08.689 --> 03:11.351
Oh, just a heads up...

03:11.359 --> 03:13.691
Call your boys down at county.

03:13.694 --> 03:16.071
Rosie Larsen files,
they up and disappeared

03:16.072 --> 03:18.108
somewhere between our house
and theirs.

03:18.741 --> 03:22.325
Guess you're in the wrong circle
of trust, Lieutenant.

03:28.376 --> 03:30.116
I need to use the phone.

03:30.795 --> 03:31.705
Please.

03:31.712 --> 03:34.203
I'd be happy to contact
a family member for you,

03:34.215 --> 03:35.625
let them know you're here.

03:36.258 --> 03:37.634
I need to talk to my partner.

03:38.219 --> 03:39.425
You can't deny me
reasonable access to a phone.

03:39.428 --> 03:41.089
Of course,
but you'll have to wait

03:41.097 --> 03:43.588
to make a personal phone call
during the designated hours.

03:43.599 --> 03:45.635
But this isn't a personal call.

03:46.519 --> 03:48.384
l have important information
regarding a case

03:48.396 --> 03:50.387
that needs to be relayed
to my partner.

03:50.398 --> 03:52.389
Right now you are impeding
a murder investigation.

03:52.400 --> 03:56.063
Sarah...
The rules are in place.

03:56.070 --> 03:57.560
That's fine.
I'll write him a note.

03:57.571 --> 03:58.902
No, if you want to
write him a note,

03:59.907 --> 04:02.899
I'll make sure he gets it.

04:02.910 --> 04:06.073
When was the last time
you ate something?

04:06.080 --> 04:08.366
- Slept?
- I don't have to be in here.

04:08.749 --> 04:10.740
You're on suicide watch, Sarah.

04:11.752 --> 04:13.868
It's only for 72 hours.

04:14.630 --> 04:16.712
Maybe you should get some rest.

04:24.223 --> 04:27.056
I'm sorry I yelled at you.
I shouldn't have done that.

04:27.059 --> 04:28.299
You were right, Terry.

04:28.310 --> 04:30.392
l was so busy
feeling sorry for myself

04:30.396 --> 04:33.058
I couldn't see
what was happening to the boys.

04:33.065 --> 04:35.977
Even before Rosie...

04:36.235 --> 04:38.567
I acted like if...

04:38.571 --> 04:41.233
| pretended like everything
was okay, it would be.

04:41.240 --> 04:43.652
You're being too hard
on yourself, Stan.

04:45.077 --> 04:47.159
Tommy killed some birds
at school today.

04:47.163 --> 04:49.074
He's suspended for two weeks.

04:49.081 --> 04:50.912
He's angry...

04:52.126 --> 04:54.959
With everything
that's happening.

04:54.962 --> 04:56.623
Mitch leaving.

04:56.630 --> 04:59.588
| just don't know
what else to do.

05:04.805 --> 05:06.761
Stan...

05:09.602 --> 05:14.016
What happens if the cops
never find the guy?

05:15.733 --> 05:18.896
[Sighs]

05:18.903 --> 05:22.066
You're angry
'cause you can't let go.

05:25.201 --> 05:26.691
The boys can see it.

05:28.913 --> 05:30.904
They're holding their breath

05:30.915 --> 05:33.702
wondering when it'll be okay
to start living again.

05:36.128 --> 05:39.495
You got to try, Stan.

05:39.507 --> 05:42.840
How do I do that?

05:42.843 --> 05:46.506
Maybe you fix what you can.

05:46.514 --> 05:48.470
And I don't know.

05:54.563 --> 05:58.522
Maybe then you
forgive yourself.

06:20.005 --> 06:21.961
[ Electricity buzzes]

06:24.468 --> 06:26.800
[ Groans ]

06:26.804 --> 06:29.637
Love you. Bye.

06:29.640 --> 06:31.676
- See you later.
- Okay.

06:33.394 --> 06:35.760
- Have a good day.
- Bye.

06:36.105 --> 06:38.061
[ Door closes]

07:01.338 --> 07:04.705
Hey, you Regi?

07:06.510 --> 07:08.592
Can I help you?

07:09.263 --> 07:12.505
Yeah, I'm...
l'm Stephen Holder.

07:12.516 --> 07:14.928
Linden's partner.

07:14.935 --> 07:16.596
Sarah found evidence
in that casino

07:16.604 --> 07:18.515
linking Rosie Larsen's death
to city hall.

07:18.522 --> 07:20.433
Now they got her locked up
for three days

07:20.441 --> 07:22.181
until the election's over

07:22.192 --> 07:24.604
and the case is buried
for good.

07:24.612 --> 07:28.776
And... what... what is it
that you want me to do?

07:28.782 --> 07:31.945
Well, could you call someone,
pull some strings?

07:31.952 --> 07:34.614
I thought you worked
in Social Services or something.

07:34.622 --> 07:36.738
Well, other than
the hospital doctors,

07:36.749 --> 07:40.082
the only person that can get her
released is her psychiatrist.

07:40.085 --> 07:43.577
Okay. W-who is she?
You got her number?

07:43.589 --> 07:45.329
I can't give you
that information,

07:45.341 --> 07:47.548
and I'm pretty sure
Sarah wouldn't want me to.

07:47.551 --> 07:49.052
There's proof in that casino

07:49.053 --> 07:50.634
proving that Sarah isn't crazy

07:50.638 --> 07:52.549
and how this all connects
to the mayor.

07:52.556 --> 07:54.968
Did... did you see the proof...
with your own eyes,

07:54.975 --> 07:57.307
or is that just
what Sarah told you?

07:57.311 --> 07:59.302
Come on.

07:59.313 --> 08:02.305
I can see that you care
about her. So do |.

08:02.316 --> 08:04.102
You're the only family
she's got.

08:04.109 --> 08:06.191
And I don't like it
that she's in there

08:06.195 --> 08:07.685
and she doesn't want to be.

08:07.696 --> 08:09.357
But I've seen
what she does to herself.

08:09.365 --> 08:11.731
Who's taking care of Jack?

08:12.034 --> 08:14.195
He's in Chicago with his dad.

08:14.203 --> 08:16.364
[ Scoffs ]

08:16.372 --> 08:18.704
Work is the last thing
that she needs right now.

08:18.707 --> 08:21.824
It's why she got put in there
in the first place.

08:21.835 --> 08:23.666
I've seen what happens to her

08:23.671 --> 08:25.787
when she neglects
everything else in her life.

08:25.798 --> 08:27.834
When she thinks
that she needs that case

08:27.841 --> 08:29.627
more than she needs sleep
or food,

08:29.635 --> 08:31.421
more than her own son.

08:33.305 --> 08:36.638
This is... this is how
it started the last time.

08:36.642 --> 08:38.928
Well, this time is different.

08:56.203 --> 08:58.990
[ Seagull cries ]

09:26.316 --> 09:27.601
[ lnhales deeply]

09:27.609 --> 09:29.565
[Speed-dialing, ringing]

09:32.072 --> 09:33.403
Ray: Yeah.

09:33.407 --> 09:35.944
- Yo, Ray, it's Holder.
- I can't be talking to you.

09:35.951 --> 09:39.114
Carlson's orders. I thought
you were on sick leave.

09:39.121 --> 09:40.531
Hey, check out something
for me.

09:40.539 --> 09:43.781
Mayor Adams, Waterfront Project,
and Michael Ames.

09:43.792 --> 09:45.703
I need any info you can get

09:45.711 --> 09:47.702
on Ames' company,
Columbia Domain Fund,

09:47.713 --> 09:48.702
and the waterfront.

09:48.714 --> 09:50.124
Like what?

09:50.132 --> 09:52.839
Looking for anything dirty...
arrests, union complaints,

09:52.843 --> 09:56.427
building code violations...
I don't know. Just do it.

09:57.347 --> 09:58.678
You there?

09:58.682 --> 10:01.389
[ Keys clacking ]
Yeah, yeah, I'm checking.

10:01.393 --> 10:03.600
One arrest at the waterfront
on record.

10:03.604 --> 10:05.265
Couple of weeks ago,
9th precinct picked up a guy

10:05.272 --> 10:06.933
who broke in.

10:06.940 --> 10:08.931
They cut him loose.
No charges.

10:08.942 --> 10:10.443
Look, you're reaching, bro.

10:10.444 --> 10:12.435
Couple of weeks ago?
What was the date?

10:12.446 --> 10:15.358
October 5th.

10:15.365 --> 10:17.356
The night Rosie Larsen
was killed.

10:17.367 --> 10:18.982
Yeah, there were dozen
other crimes that night.

10:18.994 --> 10:21.485
It doesn't mean it had anything
to do with Rosie...

10:36.595 --> 10:38.551
[ lndistinct conversation ]

10:43.602 --> 10:45.558
[ Breathing heavily]

10:48.649 --> 10:50.435
What the hell
are you doing here?

10:50.442 --> 10:53.149
Stan: Mr. Ahmed...

10:53.153 --> 10:56.145
I was wrong.

10:56.156 --> 10:59.694
I know Rosie cared for you...

10:59.701 --> 11:02.534
That she came
to say goodbye that night,

11:02.538 --> 11:03.869
and that's all.

11:03.872 --> 11:07.160
You stay away from my family,
or I'm calling the cops.

11:07.167 --> 11:09.283
Do you understand?

11:09.294 --> 11:11.751
You've done enough.

11:11.755 --> 11:14.747
Now, get out of here.

11:14.758 --> 11:17.374
Get out of here!

11:23.684 --> 11:25.640
[ Door opens ]

11:34.361 --> 11:35.521
She's right here.

11:35.529 --> 11:37.986
Okay. Thank you.

11:44.830 --> 11:47.321
I'm Dr. Kerry.

11:47.332 --> 11:48.947
It's nice to meet you.

11:48.959 --> 11:51.496
This is all a terrible mistake.
I can explain everything.

11:51.503 --> 11:53.710
Do you mind
if I call you Sarah?

11:53.714 --> 11:57.047
The nurse already told me...
You were working a case.

11:57.050 --> 11:58.711
Yes, I am.

11:58.719 --> 12:02.052
But you have been suspended
from the police department.

12:02.055 --> 12:04.387
So you can't actually
be doing that

12:04.391 --> 12:07.224
if you're no longer
a detective, can you?

12:07.227 --> 12:08.558
A few days ago,

12:08.562 --> 12:11.554
you and your son fled
from Child Protective Services

12:11.565 --> 12:14.181
who were responding
to reports of neglect.

12:14.193 --> 12:16.684
Since then, they've been unable
to locate a residence for you.

12:16.695 --> 12:18.356
Where have you been staying?

12:18.363 --> 12:19.739
At a friend's.

12:19.740 --> 12:22.573
The woman who found you
on the 10th floor of the casino

12:22.576 --> 12:24.407
said that you were
about to jump.

12:24.411 --> 12:25.912
And when she tried
to pull you back,

12:25.913 --> 12:28.245
you fought with her,
she sustained some injuries.

12:28.248 --> 12:31.536
That's not what happened.
I didn't touch her.

12:31.543 --> 12:35.001
I am not here to keep you
against your will, Sarah.

12:35.005 --> 12:36.996
- Then let me out.
- I'd like to.

12:37.007 --> 12:40.841
So if you talk to me,
then I can help you.

12:41.637 --> 12:43.502
I'll be making the
final recommendations

12:43.513 --> 12:45.765
about your release,
and so if you're cooperative,

12:45.766 --> 12:47.427
you can be out of here
a lot sooner

12:47.434 --> 12:49.641
than the 72-hour hold,
okay?

12:55.859 --> 12:59.022
Can you tell me about this?

12:59.029 --> 13:00.519
It's a photocopy

13:00.530 --> 13:03.237
of a drawing
that you brought with you

13:03.242 --> 13:05.858
last time
you were admitted here.

13:05.869 --> 13:09.157
Dr. Felder notes
that it had some significance

13:09.164 --> 13:12.156
to the case that you were
working at that time.

13:12.709 --> 13:15.951
I think that we should start
by talking about that case

13:15.963 --> 13:18.420
and the last time
you were here.

13:31.770 --> 13:36.013
Thank you. Thank you all for having me.
It's really good to be here.

13:36.024 --> 13:38.891
- Really.
- Good to see you, Councilman.

13:41.071 --> 13:43.858
Darren, we're still 7 points
down. Polls aren't budging.

13:43.865 --> 13:46.117
We should be out there courting
votes we don't already have.

13:46.118 --> 13:48.450
If we can't beat Adams
in ad space,

13:48.453 --> 13:50.409
we'll beat him
here on the ground.

13:50.414 --> 13:53.747
Okay. Well, at least one of us
should be doing real work.

13:53.750 --> 13:56.332
I'll be at the office.

13:57.129 --> 13:58.790
He'll be all right.

13:58.797 --> 14:00.128
He doesn't like to lose.

14:00.132 --> 14:02.498
Well, you two have that
in common.

14:02.509 --> 14:05.342
You're not so comfortable
with that yourself.

14:05.345 --> 14:07.006
I'm glad you're doing this.

14:07.014 --> 14:09.005
I think you should finish
the way you started.

14:09.016 --> 14:11.257
No backroom deals,
no compromises...

14:11.268 --> 14:12.474
Just being yourself.

14:12.477 --> 14:13.637
Naive?

14:13.645 --> 14:16.022
Genuine.

14:17.899 --> 14:20.311
Man: - Yo, that's out of bounds.
Woman: - Guard him!

14:20.319 --> 14:22.059
Blue ball. Blue ball.
[Laughs]

14:22.070 --> 14:24.026
Who thinks I can make a basket?

14:24.031 --> 14:25.692
[Cheers and applause] Huh?

14:25.699 --> 14:27.155
Cool.

14:27.159 --> 14:30.447
Yes, I can!

14:30.454 --> 14:32.786
You got it.

14:32.789 --> 14:34.404
Oh, no, I can't.

14:34.416 --> 14:35.531
[All groan]

14:35.834 --> 14:39.998
Didn't say I'd make it
the first time. No.

14:42.007 --> 14:43.872
[Cheers and applause]

14:43.884 --> 14:44.999
Whoo!

14:45.010 --> 14:46.796
All right, let's play!

14:48.889 --> 14:52.473
[Laughs] Here we go.

14:53.226 --> 14:55.353
Dr. Kerry: Your file says
you're a smoker.

14:55.354 --> 14:57.561
Would you like a cigarette?

14:57.564 --> 15:00.522
This office
does have some perks.

15:08.867 --> 15:13.611
So... tell me
about that case.

15:14.164 --> 15:16.029
Isn't it in the file?

15:16.041 --> 15:18.373
Mm, I'd like to hear it
from you.

15:21.421 --> 15:25.755
It was, uh, nonstop
working a murder.

15:25.759 --> 15:27.966
Every cop goes through it...
Not sleeping, not eating.

15:27.969 --> 15:30.927
But they don't all end up here.

15:31.765 --> 15:34.347
I should have taken better care
of myself, and I didn't,

15:34.351 --> 15:36.012
and that's it.

15:36.019 --> 15:37.134
[ lnhales deeply]

15:37.145 --> 15:40.683
You were brought here
by a Regi Darnell.

15:40.690 --> 15:44.683
Your 10-year—old son, Jack,
called her.

15:44.694 --> 15:47.185
He was scared.

15:47.197 --> 15:50.439
You hadn't been out of
your bedroom for several days.

15:50.450 --> 15:53.032
[ Breathes deeply]

15:53.703 --> 15:57.161
Why don't you tell me
about this drawing?

15:57.916 --> 16:01.033
I was called to the scene
by patrol.

16:01.503 --> 16:03.710
Hooker had been slashed.

16:03.713 --> 16:05.544
Killed.

16:05.549 --> 16:08.040
Her body was decomposing
in her apartment.

16:08.051 --> 16:11.043
The smell alerted
the neighbors.

16:11.388 --> 16:13.629
Her 6-year-old son
was inside.

16:13.640 --> 16:15.380
They had to break down
the front door.

16:15.392 --> 16:16.882
He couldn't reach the chain.

16:16.893 --> 16:19.384
He'd been inside with his
mother's body for a week,

16:19.396 --> 16:22.854
hiding in a closet
waiting for someone to come.

16:26.361 --> 16:27.897
I took him to the kitchen

16:27.904 --> 16:30.816
to wait for Child Protective
Services to come.

16:30.824 --> 16:34.817
He drew that...
again and again.

16:35.162 --> 16:40.156
What was his name?
The boy.

16:40.167 --> 16:42.203
Adrian.

16:42.210 --> 16:45.373
That must have been horrible...

16:45.380 --> 16:47.871
For you to see that.

16:47.883 --> 16:51.046
You've probably seen a lot
of horrible things.

16:51.052 --> 16:52.212
They must get to you.

16:52.220 --> 16:54.381
What about you?

16:54.389 --> 16:57.381
Spending your days
talking to crazy people.

16:57.392 --> 16:59.849
Hard to not let that in, right?

17:01.480 --> 17:03.971
[ lnhales sharply]

17:03.982 --> 17:06.473
Looks like trees and a hill.

17:06.485 --> 17:10.069
I mean, it's...
it's quite peaceful, actually.

17:10.614 --> 17:13.321
You don't see this image
as peaceful?

17:13.325 --> 17:15.281
Well, he drew it over and over

17:15.285 --> 17:16.775
while his mother
was rotting away

17:16.786 --> 17:18.822
in the other room, so...

17:18.830 --> 17:21.207
No, I don't.

17:21.208 --> 17:25.417
What happened to that boy?
To Adrian.

17:25.420 --> 17:28.036
He ended up
in the foster system.

17:30.425 --> 17:33.588
I'd expect more than that clumsy
cigarette move from you.

17:33.595 --> 17:35.426
But then maybe that's why
you ended up here.

17:35.430 --> 17:39.048
Bottom-of-the-barrel psych unit.
It must get to you.

17:41.895 --> 17:44.056
[ lndistinct conversations]

17:44.064 --> 17:46.897
Hey, you need to keep
blanketing downtown

17:46.900 --> 17:48.481
and Rainier Valley
with those things.

17:48.485 --> 17:50.146
It should have been
done yesterday!

17:50.153 --> 17:51.893
What the hell's wrong
with you people?

17:51.905 --> 17:53.896
Go on, get out of here!

17:53.907 --> 17:55.898
Let's go, guys.

17:55.909 --> 17:57.865
[ lndistinct conversations]

18:11.383 --> 18:14.375
Patty, come here a minute.

18:15.971 --> 18:18.587
Who closed the office
last night?

18:26.648 --> 18:28.980
Holder: You were
the arresting officer

18:28.984 --> 18:30.975
the night of October 5th?

18:30.986 --> 18:33.944
Yeah. Dep comm's
always riding us.

18:33.947 --> 18:36.359
But I got my ass chewed out
for it.

18:36.366 --> 18:38.357
You got a name on the guy
you arrested?

18:38.368 --> 18:40.529
Yeah.

18:40.537 --> 18:43.199
Joseph Nowak.

18:43.206 --> 18:45.538
Yeah, I got a noise complaint
a few blocks away.

18:45.542 --> 18:47.658
When I drove past,
I see some guy

18:47.669 --> 18:50.411
slipping under the fence
out of the construction site.

18:50.422 --> 18:53.414
- Well, what time was that?
- Around 9:30.

18:53.425 --> 18:55.916
Brought him down to the station,
let him make his call.

18:55.927 --> 18:58.760
Next thing I know, I got
the project manager calling

18:58.763 --> 19:02.130
saying the guy works for him,
telling me, "cut him loose."

19:02.142 --> 19:04.633
- You talked to Michael Ames?
- That guy's a prick.

19:04.644 --> 19:06.600
He's lying through his teeth.

19:06.605 --> 19:09.688
Whatever Nowak was doing there,
it wasn't construction.

19:09.691 --> 19:12.398
Yeah, he had a bad attitude,
smelled like a con.

19:12.402 --> 19:16.020
I ran him through CODIS...
Nowak works for the mob.

19:16.031 --> 19:18.397
Who's he work for?

19:18.408 --> 19:20.364
Janek Kovarsky.

19:28.084 --> 19:29.745
Before your suspension,

19:29.753 --> 19:32.415
you were working
on the Rosie Larsen murder case.

19:32.422 --> 19:35.459
Pretty high profile.
Lots of stress?

19:35.467 --> 19:37.128
Why are we talking about this?

19:37.135 --> 19:39.046
Well, because that's why
you're here.

19:39.054 --> 19:41.796
I thought I was here because
I was trying to kill myself.

19:47.062 --> 19:50.225
Rosie Larsen was
a 17-year—old senior...

19:50.231 --> 19:51.732
Good student,
seemingly nice family...

19:51.733 --> 19:53.143
Someone killed her,

19:53.151 --> 19:55.142
put her in the trunk of a car
and pushed it into a lake.

19:55.153 --> 19:56.893
Why do you say "seemingly"?

19:56.905 --> 20:00.568
You said,
"seemingly nice family. "

20:00.575 --> 20:02.941
We all have secrets.

20:02.952 --> 20:07.286
You, me, Larsen family,
dead girl.

20:07.290 --> 20:10.908
And that's what you do?
You find out people's secrets?

20:10.919 --> 20:12.784
They leave them behind.

20:12.796 --> 20:14.787
Sometimes it's what
got them killed.

20:14.798 --> 20:17.790
Sometimes it's just...
[Sighs]

20:17.801 --> 20:19.666
It's as though they're
trying to tell you something.

20:19.678 --> 20:21.259
The victim.

20:21.262 --> 20:24.595
Is that what Rosie Larsen
was doing?

20:24.599 --> 20:26.840
She was trying
to tell you something.

20:26.851 --> 20:32.847
She was drowned
in the trunk of a car.

20:32.857 --> 20:36.349
And you found Adrian
in a dark closet.

20:36.361 --> 20:39.023
What does that mean
to you, Sarah?

20:39.030 --> 20:41.362
Nothing.

20:41.366 --> 20:43.982
Then it's because
they were children?

20:47.497 --> 20:50.489
No, I've worked
child murders before.

20:50.500 --> 20:53.992
Then why did these two cases
mean so much to you?

21:03.179 --> 21:05.841
I've been cooperative.
I've answered your questions.

21:05.849 --> 21:09.262
Now I'd like to know
when I'm getting out of here.

21:17.944 --> 21:19.559
Let's take a break for now.

21:19.571 --> 21:22.734
No. You said all I had to do was
talk and you'd let me go.

21:22.741 --> 21:24.572
Well, I think that
you need to stay here

21:24.576 --> 21:26.737
- for a little bit longer.
- How much longer?

21:26.745 --> 21:28.235
Possibly through the end
of the week.

21:28.246 --> 21:31.579
You need to rest, eat,
get into a normal routine.

21:31.583 --> 21:33.323
You can't keep me here.
I did what you asked.

21:33.334 --> 21:35.325
I answered your questions,
and now I need to leave.

21:35.336 --> 21:37.076
It's not a punishment,
you being here, Sarah.

21:37.088 --> 21:39.079
You can't keep me here.

21:39.090 --> 21:40.751
- I need to get out of here right now.
- Sarah...

21:40.759 --> 21:42.374
You lied to me!

21:42.385 --> 21:44.171
- No, that is not true.
- Don't... don't you touch me!

21:44.179 --> 21:45.214
- That is not true. That is not true.
- Don't touch me!

21:45.221 --> 21:47.212
- Don't you touch me!
- Calm down.

21:47.223 --> 21:49.885
- What are you doing?! Let me go!
- Sarah, you need to relax.

21:49.893 --> 21:51.053
- You promised me!
- Calm down. It's gonna be...

21:51.060 --> 21:53.142
I shouldn't be here!
I shouldn't be here!

21:55.899 --> 21:58.185
All right, thank you.
Thank you for your support.

21:58.193 --> 22:00.684
Okay. Okay, bye.

22:00.695 --> 22:03.937
[Sighs]

22:05.033 --> 22:07.866
Looks like we'll be able to buy
some of that ad space

22:07.869 --> 22:10.030
the mayor hasn't
already grabbed up.

22:10.038 --> 22:11.073
And...

22:13.792 --> 22:15.783
[Sighs]

22:16.211 --> 22:17.872
Where did you get this?

22:17.879 --> 22:19.870
We're so close, Darren.

22:20.840 --> 22:23.217
The next three days
will determine this election.

22:23.218 --> 22:25.083
Jamie.

22:25.762 --> 22:27.878
I found it in here.

22:28.264 --> 22:30.755
Gwen closed the office
last night.

22:33.144 --> 22:36.181
Any idea why she'd be meeting
with the mayor?

22:38.233 --> 22:40.189
[Sighs]

22:44.948 --> 22:46.779
[Sighs]

22:46.783 --> 22:48.739
[Dialing]

22:52.038 --> 22:53.198
[Ringing]

22:53.206 --> 22:55.162
[Sighs]

23:00.046 --> 23:01.661
Rosie: Hi, it's Rosie.
I'm not around right now.

23:01.673 --> 23:04.460
But I'll be back soon.
Leave a message. Bye.

23:04.467 --> 23:06.332
I Beep ]

23:10.932 --> 23:15.221
[ Hoarsely] Hi, bean.
It's daddy.

23:21.234 --> 23:23.099
I'm calling 'cause
I don't know what else to do

23:23.111 --> 23:25.067
because...

23:27.657 --> 23:29.943
[Crying] I'm sorry.

23:36.165 --> 23:38.998
It never should have been
a secret to you...

23:39.544 --> 23:42.001
That I chose to be your dad.

23:44.966 --> 23:48.003
It was the best decision
I ever made.

23:48.011 --> 23:49.342
[Sobs softly]

23:49.888 --> 23:52.345
You've... always been...

23:53.391 --> 23:55.097
the best thing about me.

23:55.101 --> 23:57.387
The very best thing.

24:03.109 --> 24:04.770
Bye.
[ Sobs ]

24:04.777 --> 24:06.563
[ Receiver hangs up]

24:10.700 --> 24:12.656
[Seagulls squawking ]

24:16.247 --> 24:19.205
[ lndistinct conversations]

24:19.208 --> 24:22.166
Woman: Visiting hours
are almost over.

24:28.593 --> 24:29.958
Hey.

24:33.765 --> 24:35.551
How you holding up, Linden?

24:35.558 --> 24:38.015
We don't have a lot of time.
What do you got?

24:40.730 --> 24:42.891
There was a break-in
at the waterfront

24:42.899 --> 24:45.060
the night of Rosie's death.

24:45.068 --> 24:47.229
Janek Kovarsky's guy.

24:47.236 --> 24:50.569
He gets arrested.
Ames doesn't press charges.

24:50.573 --> 24:53.235
An hour later,
we got Ames canceling

24:53.242 --> 24:55.403
his weekend plans
and heading to the casino

24:55.411 --> 24:58.073
to meet with Chief Jackson,
most likely.

24:58.081 --> 25:02.040
And someone from city hall.
I saw a white key card.

25:03.586 --> 25:06.419
So they were planning something
at the waterfront,

25:06.422 --> 25:09.084
and it went wrong when
Kovarsky's guy got arrested.

25:11.678 --> 25:14.841
We're close, Linden.

25:14.847 --> 25:16.257
Hey.

25:16.975 --> 25:18.966
Hey, look at me.

25:23.481 --> 25:26.939
I saw a white key card
from city hall.

25:32.031 --> 25:34.317
What'd they do to you?

25:39.497 --> 25:41.488
Please, don't leave me here.

25:47.255 --> 25:48.916
I'm gonna get you out of here.

25:48.923 --> 25:50.629
Sir, it's time.

25:52.844 --> 25:56.007
Just hang tight
for a couple of hours.

25:56.014 --> 25:59.177
I'm not leaving you in here.

25:59.183 --> 26:02.175
You hear?
I'm not leaving you here.

26:19.996 --> 26:21.987
[ Machinery whirring]

26:21.998 --> 26:27.368
[ lndistinct conversation ]

26:29.964 --> 26:31.465
Joseph Nowak?

26:31.466 --> 26:33.457
Hey!

26:50.777 --> 26:53.234
Yeah?
Where you running, fool?

26:53.863 --> 26:54.773
Huh?

26:54.781 --> 26:56.021
Aah!
[Gun cocks]

26:56.032 --> 26:57.363
Huh?

26:57.366 --> 26:59.231
What were you doing
at the waterfront

26:59.243 --> 27:00.744
the night of October 5th?

27:00.745 --> 27:02.485
Why didn't Ames press charges?
Huh?

27:02.497 --> 27:04.704
You can't shoot me.
You're a cop.

27:04.707 --> 27:06.743
Tell me what you were doing
for Ames that night

27:06.751 --> 27:09.037
at the waterfront.

27:18.429 --> 27:19.669
Get out of my car.

27:19.680 --> 27:20.760
The night Rosie Larsen
was killed,

27:20.765 --> 27:22.426
there was a break-in
at the waterfront.

27:22.433 --> 27:24.094
All our players are involved.

27:24.102 --> 27:25.763
Janek Kovarsky's thug

27:25.770 --> 27:27.761
breaks into the mayor's
construction site.

27:27.772 --> 27:31.481
Project manager Michael Ames
chose not to press charges.

27:31.484 --> 27:32.599
So what?

27:32.610 --> 27:34.942
Here's the best part.
I spoke to Janek's boy.

27:34.946 --> 27:36.811
Says he was given an order
that night

27:36.823 --> 27:39.986
to break in and bury
some Indian bones.

27:40.326 --> 27:42.658
So Janek's boy,
he was supposed to be protected.

27:42.662 --> 27:43.993
He was gonna get in,
bury the bones,

27:43.996 --> 27:45.497
get out, inside job.

27:45.498 --> 27:47.113
Except our boys
at the 9th precinct,

27:47.125 --> 27:49.616
they weren't in on it.
They arrested him.

27:49.627 --> 27:50.958
I'm guessing our players
get scared

27:50.962 --> 27:52.702
their boy's gonna talk.

27:52.713 --> 27:54.965
They head out to the casino
to meet with Nicole Jackson.

27:55.299 --> 27:57.756
Rosie Larsen overhears
the conversation.

27:57.760 --> 27:59.341
Gets herself killed.

27:59.720 --> 28:01.176
Lieu...

28:01.597 --> 28:03.508
This goes
all the way to the top.

28:04.350 --> 28:06.807
This goes all the way
to city hall.

28:08.396 --> 28:11.433
Why would the mayor
sabotage his own project?

28:11.440 --> 28:13.567
It's the cornerstone
of his campaign.

28:13.568 --> 28:14.808
And why would Ames sabotage

28:14.819 --> 28:16.980
the biggest construction project
he's had in years?

28:16.988 --> 28:20.105
Unless they both knew
another payday'd come...

28:20.658 --> 28:22.899
And it'd be bigger.

28:23.870 --> 28:25.656
You're on the wrong side,
Lieutenant.

28:25.663 --> 28:27.324
And they're using you.

28:27.331 --> 28:29.743
I need her psychiatrist's name
and number.

28:30.751 --> 28:33.584
You've got it.
It's in her file.

28:35.548 --> 28:38.255
Let's solve this case.

28:50.521 --> 28:52.136
Gwen: Hey.

28:52.148 --> 28:53.979
Have you seen that video?

28:53.983 --> 28:56.269
Uh, what video?

28:56.277 --> 28:58.893
My in-box is flooded
with this thing.

28:58.905 --> 29:00.861
It's from the event
this morning.

29:00.865 --> 29:02.196
[ Keys clacking]

29:02.200 --> 29:04.532
It's you playing basketball
with those kids.

29:04.535 --> 29:06.446
It's gone viral.

29:06.454 --> 29:08.945
Richmond:
opportunity for healing.

29:08.956 --> 29:12.119
See, I-I find
that all adversity

29:12.126 --> 29:13.866
opens the past.

29:13.878 --> 29:16.369
Is this your work or Jamie's?

29:16.380 --> 29:17.369
Neither.

29:17.381 --> 29:18.757
Someone in the crowd
took it on a phone

29:18.758 --> 29:20.294
and put it on the internet.

29:20.301 --> 29:22.792
These people love you, Darren.
They're rooting for you.

29:22.803 --> 29:24.304
But by facing it...

29:24.305 --> 29:26.967
What's wrong?

29:26.974 --> 29:29.306
This is good for us.

29:29.310 --> 29:30.595
[ lnhales deeply]

29:33.397 --> 29:35.888
An intern found it.

29:35.900 --> 29:38.232
In here.

29:38.236 --> 29:41.194
You closed the office
last night.

29:45.409 --> 29:48.025
I asked him to meet me here.

29:49.956 --> 29:51.742
I thought...

29:53.417 --> 29:56.875
I hoped he would back off
because of what I had on him.

30:00.925 --> 30:02.711
Go ahead.

30:05.012 --> 30:06.468
[Sighs]

30:11.644 --> 30:14.010
[Sighs]

30:14.021 --> 30:15.522
The summer before high school,

30:15.523 --> 30:18.185
he was working for my father.

30:18.192 --> 30:21.184
He was over at the house
all the time.

30:21.195 --> 30:24.187
He'd ask me questions.

30:24.198 --> 30:26.655
He seemed interested in me.

30:29.078 --> 30:30.318
[Sighs]

30:30.329 --> 30:33.617
Gwen, you don't have to
tell me anything, you don't...

30:34.625 --> 30:37.241
One night we were
in the living room alone.

30:37.253 --> 30:39.665
My dad was in the kitchen.

30:40.756 --> 30:43.418
And he leaned over,

30:43.426 --> 30:45.382
and he...

30:49.181 --> 30:51.888
That was my first kiss.

30:55.980 --> 30:59.643
I was 14 years old.

30:59.650 --> 31:03.142
I want this so badly
for you, Darren.

31:03.154 --> 31:04.769
Gwen...

31:23.424 --> 31:24.880
I don't get it.

31:24.884 --> 31:27.045
[ Laughing ]
How am I so bad at this game?

31:27.053 --> 31:28.213
[ Door opens ]

31:28.220 --> 31:29.881
[ Both chuckle]

31:29.889 --> 31:31.880
Hi, dad.

31:31.891 --> 31:34.348
You want some food?

31:35.311 --> 31:38.303
Everybody close your eyes.
It's a surprise.

31:38.314 --> 31:40.020
Close your eyes.

31:41.442 --> 31:44.275
All right. Open them.
[Gasps]

31:44.278 --> 31:45.939
Denny: Sweet! Is it ours?
[ Laughs]

31:45.946 --> 31:47.937
Yeah.
It's all yours.

31:47.948 --> 31:49.688
Just don't let him
make a mess in the house.

31:49.700 --> 31:51.941
- Plus you got to feed him. You
got to walk him. - This is awesome.

31:51.952 --> 31:53.692
[Chuckling ]
He only has one eye.

31:53.704 --> 31:56.491
Maybe it's a pirate dog.

31:56.499 --> 31:58.114
- He's huge!
- Oh, yeah.

31:58.125 --> 32:01.458
- What should we name him?
- You can take care of him, bud, right?

32:01.462 --> 32:03.453
Yeah.

32:03.464 --> 32:05.295
[ Smooches ]
Denny: Yeah, awesome.

32:05.299 --> 32:06.459
Oh, my God!

32:06.467 --> 32:07.502
[ Urinating ] Whoa!

32:07.510 --> 32:09.842
- Here we go!
- Gross!

32:09.845 --> 32:11.631
Go get paper towels.
Quick, quick.

32:11.639 --> 32:13.300
Did you press a button?

32:13.307 --> 32:15.639
[Laughs] - No.
- Hurry. Toss them to me.

32:15.643 --> 32:17.554
- He's so slobbery.
- Here.

32:17.561 --> 32:19.552
Oh, my gosh.

32:19.563 --> 32:22.396
- It's right there. Right there.
- Hey, careful when you tickle him,

32:22.400 --> 32:23.890
he don't shit on the carpet,
all right?

32:23.901 --> 32:25.061
[ Laughter]

32:25.069 --> 32:27.355
Oh!

32:27.363 --> 32:29.604
- I can't believe we got a dog.
Denny: - Yeah.

33:08.320 --> 33:09.605
[ Moans softly]

33:27.256 --> 33:30.748
Sarah: How Rosie's body
was found...

33:30.759 --> 33:33.045
It doesn't make sense.

33:35.014 --> 33:37.676
Her killer chased her through
the woods for hours.

33:37.683 --> 33:40.390
He beat her.
It takes...

33:40.686 --> 33:43.177
Determination...

33:43.189 --> 33:46.181
Hate to do that.

33:46.192 --> 33:49.650
But she was alive
when she went in the water.

33:51.197 --> 33:52.858
The killer didn't want to

33:52.865 --> 33:54.571
see her eyes
when she finally died.

33:54.575 --> 33:55.860
Why?

33:59.747 --> 34:01.237
Well, how does that relate

34:01.248 --> 34:04.490
to Adrian's mother's
murder, Sarah?

34:06.545 --> 34:11.039
I don't know.
It doesn't.

34:11.050 --> 34:14.713
There's something meaningful
about these two cases,

34:14.720 --> 34:18.008
so... what is it?

34:19.934 --> 34:21.424
My old partner,

34:21.435 --> 34:23.926
he was... the primary.

34:23.938 --> 34:25.929
He was convinced
the dad was the doer.

34:25.940 --> 34:29.103
Said... dad probably panicked
and left

34:29.109 --> 34:32.727
through
the fire-escape window.

34:33.781 --> 34:35.772
Neighbors saw him
in the building

34:35.783 --> 34:37.614
20 minutes before
time of death...

34:37.618 --> 34:40.951
Heard an argument,
said they were always fighting.

34:40.955 --> 34:43.116
We put him away.

34:43.123 --> 34:45.910
So you caught the killer
in Adrian's case.

34:45.918 --> 34:48.625
The dad lived in that apartment.
He knew it was a shit hole.

34:48.629 --> 34:50.244
No one ever called the cops
on him.

34:50.256 --> 34:55.876
So why... would he leave
through a window?

34:57.513 --> 34:59.174
Risk attracting attention
on the street.

34:59.181 --> 35:03.140
Why not... walk right out
the front door?

35:07.731 --> 35:10.689
So you don't think
the father did it.

35:18.409 --> 35:21.242
No.

35:21.245 --> 35:23.110
I don't.

35:28.460 --> 35:30.587
Dr. Kerry: Did your partner
feel the same way,

35:30.588 --> 35:31.953
that you'd arrested
the wrong man?

35:31.964 --> 35:34.171
He was the primary,
more senior than me.

35:34.174 --> 35:35.505
The department was satisfied,

35:35.509 --> 35:38.342
and I gave up trying
to convince them at some point.

35:38.345 --> 35:40.677
And do you feel guilty
about that?

35:40.681 --> 35:42.512
[Sighs]

35:42.516 --> 35:44.848
I listened to them.
I should have...

35:44.852 --> 35:46.012
[Sighs]

35:46.020 --> 35:47.510
I should have listened to him.

35:47.521 --> 35:48.681
He was trying
to tell me something.

35:48.689 --> 35:50.350
I should have listened.

35:50.357 --> 35:54.771
- To who?
- To Adrian?

35:54.778 --> 35:57.861
Is that why you brought
the drawing with you last time, Sarah?

35:57.865 --> 36:01.608
He was trying to tell you
something with it?

36:01.619 --> 36:03.200
Is that why you've continued

36:03.203 --> 36:05.364
to investigate
the Rosie Larsen murder,

36:05.372 --> 36:07.658
even on suspension?

36:09.418 --> 36:13.752
They'll bury this case.
They'll make it go away.

36:13.756 --> 36:18.090
Sarah... maybe...

36:18.093 --> 36:20.755
what they went through
is something you relate to.

36:20.763 --> 36:23.596
Have you ever thought
about that?

36:23.599 --> 36:25.214
What?

36:29.313 --> 36:31.770
I told you why it matters.

36:35.194 --> 36:38.311
Let's talk about your mother.

36:38.322 --> 36:41.485
About when she abandoned you.

36:43.494 --> 36:46.657
You sit there in that chair
across from me

36:46.664 --> 36:49.622
thinking you'll get
to the heart of it.

36:49.625 --> 36:53.618
That you can help me,
that you can save me.

36:53.629 --> 36:56.291
It must feel good
thinking that.

36:56.298 --> 36:59.790
Justifying your little life
with that.

37:00.302 --> 37:01.758
[Sighs]

37:01.762 --> 37:03.798
Is that how you feel, Sarah?

37:03.806 --> 37:06.263
Hmm?
With your victims?

37:08.185 --> 37:13.521
No, they're dead.
They don't need saving anymore.

37:13.524 --> 37:17.517
She left you...
in the apartment...

37:17.528 --> 37:20.361
alone...

37:20.364 --> 37:22.901
when you were 5 years old.

37:22.908 --> 37:24.648
Do you remember that?

37:24.660 --> 37:26.321
No.

37:26.328 --> 37:29.946
Surely you must have
some memories.

37:32.626 --> 37:34.833
The lights had been turned off.
She hadn't paid the bill.

37:34.837 --> 37:37.294
That's all I remember.

37:39.216 --> 37:43.175
CPS found you the next morning
after she left.

37:45.597 --> 37:48.760
So you spent the night
in that place alone?

37:48.767 --> 37:51.258
That was a long time ago.
I'm fine now.

37:51.270 --> 37:52.601
[ Breathes raggedly]

37:52.604 --> 37:55.266
Your son is gone.

37:55.274 --> 37:57.265
You were supposed to be married
a few days ago.

37:57.276 --> 38:00.564
You've lost your job.
Really?

38:03.073 --> 38:04.734
Whatever you want me to say,
I'll say it.

38:04.742 --> 38:06.698
[Voice breaking ]
Just please let me go.

38:11.457 --> 38:14.699
Then you spent the night alone
in the dark...

38:30.476 --> 38:31.886
[ Knock on door, door opens]

38:31.894 --> 38:33.634
Ellen:
Excuse me, Dr. Kerry?

38:33.645 --> 38:35.431
Give us a second, please.

38:35.439 --> 38:37.896
Sarah's being
officially released.

38:37.900 --> 38:42.439
She'll be...
out in a minute.

38:46.200 --> 38:49.658
Sarah, go ahead.
What were you going to say?

39:23.654 --> 39:25.610
She know I'm here?

39:27.157 --> 39:29.489
No.

39:29.493 --> 39:32.485
I'll help get her out,

39:32.496 --> 39:35.954
but I can't be involved
anymore.

39:35.958 --> 39:37.949
She's your responsibility now.

39:41.463 --> 39:42.703
I'm Dr. Felder.

39:42.714 --> 39:44.875
